modules.description: This module implements a set-based interface for tracking visited basic blocks during Primus execution. It supports membership checks, addition, and removal of specific term IDs (TIDs) from the visited set, along with retrieving the full set of visited blocks. Direct use cases include querying whether a specific block has been executed, manually marking blocks as visited or unvisited, and obtaining a snapshot of all visited blocks at any point in the analysis.

This module implements a set-based interface for tracking visited basic blocks during Primus execution. It supports membership checks, addition, and removal of specific term IDs (TIDs) from the visited set, along with retrieving the full set of visited blocks. Direct use cases include querying whether a specific block has been executed, manually marking blocks as visited or unvisited, and obtaining a snapshot of all visited blocks at any point in the analysis.

Tracks execution of basic blocks during Primus analysis by maintaining a set of visited term IDs. It marks blocks as visited or dead, supports membership checks, additions, and removals on the visited set, and reports progress when new blocks are executed. Directly used to query execution status of specific blocks, manually adjust visitation state, and capture snapshots of visited blocks during analysis.
